  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile)",
  "description": "This unit of assurance packages credibility evidence for a CFD-based hemolysis prediction model applied to the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump. The model has been applied in clinical research contexts to support ventricular assist device (VAD) design evaluation, and the assessment team has used it to inform decisions about rotor geometry under physiologically realistic operating conditions. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed across key boundary conditions. Thirteen credibility factors were reviewed; seven received formal assessment and six were flagged as epistemic gaps. The overall evidence package is presented under the Minimal profile, with narrative scope description embedded in this field rather than in a structured ContextOfUse object.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-mrl5-req-001",
